### Email Verification & Login OTP Endpoints

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@email = aethronex@gmail.com
@otp = 706913

### 1. Send Email OTP (Verification)
### Sends a 6-digit OTP to verify the user's email
### Rate limit: 1 request per minute per email
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/send-email-otp-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "olusolasamson18@gmail.com"
}

### Expected Response (Success):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "OTP sent successfully to your email",
#   "expiresIn": "10 minutes"
# }

### Expected Response (Already Verified):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "Email is already verified",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }

### Expected Response (User Not Found):
# {
#   "statusCode": 404,
#   "message": "User not found with this email",
#   "error": "Not Found"
# }

### Expected Response (Rate Limited):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "Please wait 45 seconds before requesting a new OTP",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }


### 2. Verify Email OTP (Verification)
### Verifies the OTP and marks email as verified
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/verify-email-otp-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "otp": "{{otp}}"
}

### Expected Response (Success):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Email verified successfully",
#   "isVerified": true
# }

### Expected Response (Invalid OTP):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "Invalid OTP. Please check and try again",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }

### Expected Response (Expired OTP):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "OTP has expired. Please request a new one",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }

### Expected Response (No OTP Found):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "No OTP found. Please request a new OTP",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }

### Expected Response (Already Verified):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "Email is already verified",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }


### 3. Resend Email OTP (Login)
### Sends a 6-digit OTP to login without password
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/resend-email-otp-login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "loginuser@example.com"
}

### Expected Response (Success):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "OTP sent successfully to your email",
#   "expiresIn": "10 minutes"
# }


### 4. Verify Email OTP (Login)
### Verifies the OTP for login and returns JWT + user profile
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/verify-email-otp-login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "otp": "{{otp}}"
}

### Expected Response (Success):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "requiresOTP": false,
#   "token": "<jwt-token>",
#   "data": {
#     "_id": "...",
#     "firstName": "John",
#     "lastName": "Doe",
#     "username": "johndoe",
#     "email": "john@example.com",
#     "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
#     "role": "user"
#   },
#   "message": "Login successful"
# }

### Expected Error Responses:
# 400 Invalid/Expired/No OTP
# 404 User not found


### 5. Check Email Verification Status
### Checks if an email is verified
GET {{baseUrl}}/verification/email-status?email={{email}}

### Expected Response (Verified):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "isVerified": true,
#   "email": "john.smith@example.com"
# }

### Expected Response (Not Verified):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "isVerified": false,
#   "email": "john.smith@example.com"
# }

### Expected Response (User Not Found):
# {
#   "statusCode": 404,
#   "message": "User not found with this email",
#   "error": "Not Found"
# }


